I've addressed your round-0 findings on a follow-up branch (not merged yet). Summary:

1. Bug fixed: extracted a planner _readback() helper. The terminal-state arm now explicitly handles 'prior is None' as a transport-flavored 'store invariant violation' banner before the equivalence check, matching the implementer/evaluator. Conflict is reserved for non-equivalent prior submissions.
2. Risk fixed: the planner _readback now branches state=='claimed' (with our token vs other token) and state=='pending' (reclaimed) explicitly. State==claimed with our token surfaces the transport class name; state==claimed with a different token surfaces 'eden://error/wrong-token'; state==pending surfaces 'task reclaimed: <class>'. Tests cover all three.

New tests added to test_planner_flow.py::TestIllegalTransitionReadback:
- test_terminal_state_with_no_submission_renders_transport_invariant (asserts NO 'conflicting-resubmission' in output)
- test_pending_after_illegal_transition_distinct_from_claimed (asserts 'task reclaimed' in banner)
- test_claimed_with_other_token_renders_wrong_token (asserts wire-error string)

Files changed: routes/planner.py (_retry_submit refactored to call new _readback helper), tests/test_planner_flow.py (3 new sub-cases). Full suite 559 + 5 e2e + the new 3 = 565 passing locally.

Please re-review the planner side to confirm the Â§K-2 contract is now fully covered.
